ppening alot. Since then, windows had reported that my &quot;driver letters&quot; were not working correctly. Even though windows showed them in the My Computer section, I could not do anything that dealt with partitions. Since I no longer had my Linux partition (didn't get a chance to reformat it totally for NTFS), I no longer had a boot manager either. In DOS, it showed I still had my info on my hard disk, but I had no way to access it. Windows would not reinstall due to my drive letters being messed up. I eventually reformatted with Win2kPro, but was having this weird problem of my computer locking up whenever I was downloading anything. And, due to the drive letters being messed up, I was not able to repartition that 5 gigs still, nor was I able to scandisk or defrag. That was problem #1.<br><br>2) Problem 2 came when I bought a new 40 gig hard drive the other day. I wanted to format it, make it my primary, ghost the info from my 20 gig to my 40 gig and put a new OS on the 20 gig (dual booting again). I couldn't use Partition Magic, because of the drive letters. I couldn't use the windows computer manager to fdisk the drive, because of the drive letters, and I'm not really experienced with fdisk. Finally, I bumbled through the DOS fdisk enough to get my 40 gig partitioned for fat32, but windows still wouldn't let me format it. It kept saying &quot;Unable to determine correct space&quot;, or something like that.<br><br>3) I bought Lindows, and wanted to put it on the 2nd drive, as described above, but couldn't get it to work because of the NTFS on the 20 gig drive.<br><br>So, I decided to scrap the whole thing and start over. I plopped my Windows2k disk in, and it took care of the whole thing. The only thing I didn't like is that it formatted the 40 gig drive NTFS, and I wanted FAT32, but it didn't give me the option. I still want to put Lindows on the 20 gig, but because its a Linux based OS, it says its incompatible with Win2k. So, right now I'm installing Partition Magic pro again, and I'm going to try to convert the NTFS into FAT32, and format the 2nd drive for Linux partitioning. Going to see if that works.<br><br>Any ideas with getting Linux to sit side by side with Win2k would be appreciated. We did it on my friends computer, but I forgot how we did it.  =(<br><br>Yours, Suntoucher <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub29.ezboard.com/uleomarth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leomarth</A> at: 2/14/02 3:11:30 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub29.ezboard.com/fpaxfamillafrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=748.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub29.ezboard.com/fpaxfamillafrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=748.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/oceana/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub29.ezboard.com/fpaxfamillafrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=748.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub29.ezboard.com/fpaxfamillafrm1.threadControl?topicID=748.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/oceana/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub29.ezboard.com/fpaxfamillafrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=748.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub29.ezboard.com/fpaxfamillafrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=748.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub29.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><s